Plotting Two Datasets on the Same Chart

Key Questions

How could I compare APPL stock price with a graph of GDP or the Stock Market in the same periods, on the same image? The csv would be a separate file, and I believe, data frame…

Load the library - ggplot2 and RCurl

library(RCurl)
## Loading required package: bitops
library(ggplot2)

Start with reading AAPL price and S&P500 price from an API e.g. quandl

x <- getURL('https://www.quandl.com/api/v1/datasets/GOOG/NASDAQ_AAPL.csv')
AAPL <- read.csv(text = x, header = TRUE)

Plot on separate charts

ggplot(data = AAPL) + aes(y = Close, x = Date) + 
  geom_line() + labs(title = "Apple")

ggplot(data = SP500) + aes(y = Close, x = Date) +
  geom_line() + labs(title = "S&P 500")

Combine and plot on one charts

Do we need to scale the data?

ggplot(data = AAPL) + aes(y = Close, x = Date) + geom_line(colour = "red") + 
  geom_line(data = SP500) + aes(y = Close, x = Date) +
  labs(title = "Apple and S&P500")

Index and then plot the data

We index the data - based on the price on the 1980-12-12

AAPL$Index <- AAPL$Close / AAPL$Close[AAPL$Date == "1980-12-12"] * 100
SP500$Index <- SP500$Close / SP500$Close[SP500$Date == "1980-12-12"] * 100

ggplot(data = AAPL) + aes(y = Index, x = Date) + geom_line(colour = "red") + 
  geom_line(data = SP500) + aes(y = Index, x = Date) +
  labs(title = "Apple and S&P500 - Indexed")
